    <section id="rendering" class="tutorial-section">
        <h2>5. Rendering Modes in .NET 10</h2>
        <p>.NET 10 Blazor introduces unified render modes for flexible deployment:</p>
        
        <div class="render-mode-grid">
            <div class="render-mode-card">
                <h4>Static SSR</h4>
                <p>Pre-rendered HTML, no interactivity. Best for SEO-focused pages.</p>
                <code>@@rendermode @(new InteractiveServerRenderMode(prerender: true))</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="render-mode-card highlight">
                <h4>Interactive Server</h4>
                <p>Real-time SignalR connection. Great for internal apps.</p>
                <code>@@rendermode InteractiveServer</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="render-mode-card">
                <h4>Interactive WebAssembly</h4>
                <p>Runs in browser via WASM. Works offline.</p>
                <code>@@rendermode InteractiveWebAssembly</code>
            </div>
            
            <div class="render-mode-card">
                <h4>Auto</h4>
                <p>Starts with Server, switches to WASM after download.</p>
                <code>@@rendermode InteractiveAuto</code>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

